okay, so the bug is happening <https://github.com/singularityware/singularity/blob/development/src/lib/runtime/overlayfs/overlayfs.c#L99|here> and specifically:

```        singularity_message(VERBOSE, "Mounting overlay with options: %s\n", overlay_options);
        if ( mount("overlay", mount_final, "overlay", MS_NOSUID, overlay_options) &lt; 0 ){
            singularity_message(ERROR, "Could not mount overlayFS: %s\n", strerror(errno));
            ABORT(255); 
        }
```
which means that ` mount("overlay", mount_final, "overlay", MS_NOSUID, overlay_options` is &lt;0 and triggering the error message. Our variables are:

• mount_final: which we see is `/var/lib/singularity/mnt/final`
• overlay_options: (in this string) `Mounting overlay with options: lowerdir=/var/lib/singularity/mnt/source,upperdir=/var/lib/singularity/mnt/overlay/upper,workdir=/var/lib/singularity/mnt/overlay/work`

Could you do `--debug` for the working case so we can compare how those two are different? If they aren't different then we will keep working backwards until we find the difference :)

